ce:section.ce:para:
The absorption and fluorescence spectra of systems containing pyridinic (Fig. 7
                        ) and pyrrolic nitrogen (Fig. 8
                        ) were blue-shifted with respect to the –NH2 systems, regardless of hydration. These blue-shifts were more significant when the systems that include double substitutions or doping were compared – the absorption band center positions shifted from 333nm (342nm) in P-2NH2 to 309nm (314nm) and 298nm (309nm) in P-2pl-N and P-2pd-N in a vacuum (water), respectively. In the systems that included single substitutions or doping, the low energy absorption bands were rather closely packed, i.e. the maxima appeared at 312nm (316nm), 313nm (319nm), and 305nm (313nm) for P-1NH2, P-1pl-N, and P-1pd-N, respectively, in a vacuum (water). These findings imply that amine group functionalization and pyridinic/pyrrolic nitrogen doping in N-CDs exhibit doping element concentration dependent properties.
